---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { STARTER_MODELS } from '../data/models';
---

<Base
  title="Supported models — Dhruva AI"
  description="Verified starter models for Dhruva AI: repo IDs, sizes, and RAM guidance for on-device GGUF chat, vision, and embedding models."
>
  <header class="page-head">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Models</p>
      <h1>Bring any GGUF. Start with these.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Dhruva can load any quantized GGUF model you download from Hugging Face — there's no
        curated-only walled garden. The table below is the starter catalog: models we've verified
        work well on-device, with real repo IDs and honest RAM guidance.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="table-scroll">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">Model</th>
              <th scope="col">Repo</th>
              <th scope="col">Role</th>
              <th scope="col">Quant</th>
              <th scope="col">Approx. size</th>
              <th scope="col">RAM floor</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {
              STARTER_MODELS.map((m) => (
                <tr>
                  <td>
                    <span class="model-name">{m.name}</span>
                    <span class="use-case">{m.useCase}</span>
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <a href={`https://huggingface.co/${m.repo}`} rel="noopener" class="mono">
                      {m.repo}
                    </a>
                  </td>
                  <td>{m.role}</td>
                  <td class="mono">{m.quant}</td>
                  <td>{m.approxSize}</td>
                  <td>
                    <span class:list={['tier', { negligible: m.ramFloor === 'negligible' }]}>
                      {m.ramFloor}
                    </span>
                  </td>
                </tr>
              ))
            }
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="table-note">
        Sizes are approximate Q4_K_M file sizes at time of writing — always check the exact size
        on the model's Hugging Face page before downloading, especially on a metered connection.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section verdicts">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <h2>How device verdicts work</h2>
      <p>
        When you open a model in the hub, Dhruva shows a verdict badge — <strong>Comfortable</strong>, <strong>Possible</strong>, or <strong>Not recommended</strong> — instead of making you guess whether it'll run. The logic is deliberately simple and file-size-based, not a black box:
      </p>
      <ol class="verdict-steps">
        <li>
          Dhruva looks at the quantized <strong>file size</strong> of the GGUF you're about to download and buckets it: up to 1.2&nbsp;GB is the "1B class", up to 3&nbsp;GB is the "3B class", anything larger is "4B+".
        </li>
        <li>
          Each bucket has a RAM floor: <strong>4&nbsp;GB</strong> for the 1B class, <strong>6&nbsp;GB</strong> for the 3B class, <strong>8&nbsp;GB</strong> for 4B+.
        </li>
        <li>
          Your device's total RAM is compared against that floor. Below the floor → <strong>Not recommended</strong> (loading may run out of memory). At or above the floor but under 1.5&times; the floor → <strong>Possible</strong> (it'll run, with little headroom — expect it to be slower or crowd out other apps). At 1.5&times; the floor or above → <strong>Comfortable</strong>.
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        File size, not parameter count, drives the bucket — a Q4_K_M quant tracks real memory
        pressure much more closely than the model's advertised parameter count does. Vision models
        include their mmproj file in the size that gets bucketed, since it's loaded alongside the
        base model.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-head {
    padding-block: var(--space-4xl) var(--space-2xl);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-outline-variant);
  }

  .page-head h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-family-display);
    font-weight: var(--text-display-small-weight);
    font-size: var(--text-display-small-size);
    line-height: var(--text-display-small-line-height);
    color: var(--color-on-background);
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-base);
    max-width: 18ch;
  }

  .lede {
    max-width: 60ch;
    color: var(--color-on-surface-variant);
    font-size: var(--text-body-large-size);
  }

  .section {
    padding-block: var(--space-4xl);
  }

  .table-scroll {
    overflow-x: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-outline-variant);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }

  table {
    min-width: 48rem;
  }

  th,
  td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-base);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-outline-variant);
    font-size: var(--text-body-medium-size);
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  thead th {
    font-size: var(--text-label-medium-size);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--color-on-surface-variant);
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  tbody tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  tbody tr:hover {
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  .model-name {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-on-background);
  }

  .use-case {
    display: block;
    color: var(--color-on-surface-variant);
    font-size: var(--text-body-small-size);
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .mono {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: var(--text-body-small-size);
    color: var(--color-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    word-break: break-word;
  }

  .mono:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .tier {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-sm);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    background: var(--color-primary-container);
    color: var(--color-on-primary-container);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-label-small-size);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .tier.negligible {
    background: var(--color-surface-variant);
    color: var(--color-on-surface-variant);
  }

  .table-note {
    margin-top: var(--space-base);
    font-size: var(--text-body-small-size);
    color: var(--color-on-surface-variant);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .verdicts {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-outline-variant);
  }

  .verdict-steps {
    counter-reset: step;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-base);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .verdict-steps li {
    counter-increment: step;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: var(--space-2xl);
    color: var(--color-on-surface-variant);
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .verdict-steps li::before {
    content: counter(step);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    width: 1.5rem;
    height: 1.5rem;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    background: var(--color-primary-container);
    color: var(--color-on-primary-container);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-label-small-size);
  }
</style>
